8 An Act relating to non-opioid treatment; defining
terms; authorizing insurers to amend preferred drug
9 lists; allowing for discretion in drug treatment;
prohibiting certain drugs over others for treatment;
10 allowing coverage of drugs once approved by the
United States Food and Drug Administration;
11 authorizing coverage of non-opioid drugs; authorizing
reimbursement to hospitals for non-opioid treatment;
12 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1313.1 of Title 74, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. As used in this section:
20 1. "Group insurance plan" means a group insurance plan that
21 covers state employees;
22 2. "Health care prescriber" means an individual authorized by
23 law to prescribe drugs;
24
